Required for email/password auth:

BETTER_AUTH_SECRET — Generate one by running:
DATABASE_URL — Your real PostgreSQL connection string
Required for Google OAuth:

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID — From Google Cloud Console → Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET — Same place
Set the authorized redirect URI in Google Console to: http://localhost:3001/api/auth/callback/google

Required for emails (verification, password reset):

RESEND_API_KEY — From resend.com/api-keys
Required for payments:

PESAPAL_CONSUMER_KEY / PESAPAL_CONSUMER_SECRET — From your PesaPal dashboard
Once you have the values, update your .env file with the real keys, then restart the dev server (npm run dev). Email/password sign-up needs at minimum DATABASE_URL and BETTER_AUTH_SECRET. Google OAuth additionally needs the Google credentials.


Required steps after adding keys:

  Create database tables: npx prisma db push

Seed initial data (contestants, categories, event info): npm run db:seed

Start the app: npm run dev

Google Cloud Console — you must also add the redirect URhttp://localhost:3001/api/auth/callback/google




Create a user via the better-auth sign-up API (so the password is properly hashed)
Set the user's role to admin in the database
Default credentials (customizable via env vars):

Email: admin@ekq.com
Password: Admin@2026!


Custom credentials:
ADMIN_EMAIL=you@example.com ADMIN_PASSWORD=YourSecurePass123! npm run db:seed-admin